DIPLOMACY PEACE WAR ALLIANCE TRUCE DISTRUST

Usage:  diplomacy <option> <empire>

This command is the basis for the interaction among empires. It allows an
empire to voice its political opinion on another empire and announce it to
that empire.

You can only burn down or besiege another empires buildings if you are at war.
You can only go to war with or steal from an empire if at least one of their
members is online.

Options:
  peace    - an end to a war, or a good starting relationship
  war*     - a state of supreme distrust and hate
             depending on the pk option set on the mud, you may only be able
             to kill someone from an empire you're at war with
  ally     - share facilities and friendship
  pact     - non-aggression pact, prevents guard towers from shooting and
             demonstrates a mutual trust
  trade    - purely a cosmetic attribute, but demonstrates an agreement to
             exchange goods and services
  distrust - a state just short of war which indicates hatred
  truce    - ends a war or distrustful state without creating peace

* To declare war, an empire must immediately spend an amount of money based
on the difference between the two empires' composite scores. You can see the
cost to declare war on the empire detail page for any empire you're not in
a non-aggression pact (or better) with.

See also: EMPIRE SCORE
